  "prompt": "My username is no longer available on Skype. Why?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why your username is no longer available on Skype:\n\n1. **Username Change**: If the username was changed by you or someone else who had access to your account, the previous username would become unavailable.\n   \n2. **Account Deletion**: If the account associated with that username was deleted, the username might become unavailable.\n\n3. **Username Policy Violation**: The username might have violated Skype's policy, causing it to be blocked or removed.\n\n4. **Technical Issues**: There could be technical issues with Skype that are causing your username to appear unavailable.\n\n5. **Security Concerns**: It's possible that your account was compromised and Skype has taken action to protect it, resulting in the username being unavailable.\n\nTo resolve the issue, you may want to contact Skype's customer support for further assistance. They can provide specific information regarding your account and help you recover or understand why the username is no longer available.",
